ptember 29, 2018}}</ref> On September 27, a second, smaller spot fire had broken out to the south of the larger spot fire, situated south of Damnation Creek, which was estimated at {{convert|14|acres|km2}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://krcrtv.com/news/shasta-county/delta-fire-update-thursday-september-27-acreage-grows-from-aerial-mapping|title=Delta Fire Update Thursday, September 27: Aerial mapping shows more accurate acreage|author=Christian Wohlfeil|publisher=KCRC|date=September 27, 2018|accessdate=September 28, 2018}}</ref> The first spot fire continued to spread uncontained, while the main body of the Delta Fire was contained; by September 29, the first spot fire had exceeded {{convert|2,376|acres|km2}} in size, increasing the total burn area of the Delta Fire to {{convert|63,093|acres|km2}}, and dropping the overall containment of the Delta Fire to 97%. The spot fires were at 0% containment.<ref name=\"September 29 update\">{{cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/article/6191/48464/|title=Delta Fire Update for September 29th, 2018|author=|website=inciweb.nwcg.gov|date=September 29, 2018|accessdate=September 30, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Delta Fire\" /> On September 30, the Delta Fire expanded to {{convert|63,293|acres|km2}}, with containment remaining at 97%.<ref name=\"September 30 update\">{{cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/article/6191/48491/|title=Delta Fire Daily Update for Sunday, September 30th|author=|website=inciweb.nwcg.gov|date=September 30, 2018|accessdate=October 1, 2018}}</ref> The fire did not experience any further growths for the next several days, while containment generally remained at 97% up until October 5.<ref name=\"October 5 update\">{{cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/article/6191/48600/|title=Delta Fire Update for Friday, October 5, 2018|author=|website=inciweb.nwcg.gov|date=October 5, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2018}}</ref> Afterward, the Delta Fire experienced another small growth, increasing to {{convert|63,311|acres|km2}}. On October 7, the Delta Fire was fully contained, without any further increases in size.<ref name=\"October 7 update\">{{cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/article/6191/48631/|title=Delta Fire Update for October 7, 2018|author=|website=inciweb.nwcg.gov|date=October 7, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe fire was determined to be man-made, although the exact cause remains unclear.<ref>https://www.abc10.com/article/news/local/delta-fire-latest-maps-and-road-closures/591289213</ref>\n\n==Fire growth and containment progress==\n[[File:After a wildfire is out, our Burned Area Emergency Response teams assess dama....webm|thumb|right|Video from the [[US Forest Service]] about the Delta / Herz fires]]\n[[File:Hot shot spraying water on the Delta Fire (42894188060).jpg|thumb|Fire suppression efforts on September 14]]\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: right;\"\n|+Fire containment status<ref>{{cite web |title=Incident information - Delta Fire |publisher=InciWeb |url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/6191/}}</ref><br /><span style=\"color:#FFFFFF; background:#808080\">Gray</span>: contained; <span style=\"color:#FFFFFF; background:#FF0000\">Red</span>: active; %: percent contained;\n|-\n!Date\n!Area burned<br />acres (hectares) !!Containment\n|-\n|Sept 5||{{convert|5,000|acre|ha|abbr=values|0}}||style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{percentile|0|width=20|height=15|text-size=10|progress-done-colour=grey|progress-tbd-colour=red|text-colour=white}}\n|-\n|Sept 6||{{convert|22,000|acre|ha|abbr=values|0}}||style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{percentile|0|width=88|height=15|text-size=10|progress-done-colour=grey|progress-tbd-colour=red|text-colour=white}}\n|-\n|Sept 7||{{convert|31,325|acre|ha|abbr=values|0}}||style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{percentile|0|width=125|height=15|text-size=10|progress-done-colour=grey|progress-tbd-colour=red|text-colour=white}}\n|-\n|Sept 8||{{convert|40,580|acre|ha|abbr=values|0}}||style=\"text-align: left;\"|{{perc