 Concepts and Issues\n| edition=3rd\n| location=London\n| publisher=SAGE Publications\n| pages=107\u2013123\n| isbn=978-1-4129-0170-3\n| ref=harv\n}}\n* {{cite book\n| last=McAnulla\n| first=Stuart\n| year=2006\n| title=British Politics: A Critical Introduction\n| location=London\n| publisher=Continuum International Publishing Group\n| isbn=978-0-8264-6156-8\n| ref=harv\n}}\n* {{cite book\n| last=McClintock\n| first=John\n| year=2010\n| title=The Uniting of Nations: An Essay on Global Governance\n| edition=3rd\n| location=Brussels\n| publisher=Peter Lang\n| isbn=978-90-5201-588-0\n| ref=harv\n}}\n* {{cite book\n| last=McIlroy\n| first=John\n| year=2011\n| chapter=Britain: How Neo-Liberalism Cut Unions Down to Size\n| editor1-last=Gall\n| editor1-first=Gregor\n| editor1-link=Gregor Gall\n| editor2-last=Wilkinson\n| editor2-first=Adrian\n| editor3-last=Hurd\n| editor3-first=Richard\n| editor3-link=Richard Hurd (educator)\n| title=The International Handbook of Labour Unions: Responses to Neo-Liberalism\n| location=Cheltenham\n| publisher=Edward Elgar Publishing\n| pages=82\u2013104\n| isbn=978-1-84844-862-9\n| ref=harv\n}}\n* {{cite book\n| last1=Merkel\n| first1=Wolfgang\n| last2=Petring\n| first2=Alexander\n| last3=Henkes\n| first3=Christian\n| last4=Egle\n| first4=Christoph\n| year=2008\n| title=Social Democracy in Power: The Capacity to Reform\n| location=London\n| publisher=Taylor & Francis\n| isbn=978-0-415-43820-9\n| ref=harv\n}}\n* {{cite book\n| last=Pugh\n| first=Martin\n| authorlink = Martin Pugh (author)\n| year=2011\n| origyear=2010\n| title=Speak for Britain! A New History of the Labour Party\n| location=London\n| publisher=Vintage Books\n| isbn=978-0-09-952078-8\n| ref=harv\n| title-link=Speak for Britain!\n}}\n* {{cite book\n| last1=Rentoul\n| first1=John\n| author1-link=John Rentoul\n| year=2001\n| title=Tony Blair: Prime Minister\n| location=London\n| publisher=Little, Brown and Company\n| isbn=978-0-316-85496-2\n| ref=harv\n}}\n* {{cite journal\n| la