n{{see also|European Parliament|Elections to the European Parliament}}\nElections to the European Parliament began in 1979, and were held under the [[First-past-the-post voting|first past the post]] system until 1999, when a form of [[proportional representation]] was introduced.\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Leader\n!% share of votes\n!Seats\n!Change\n!Position\n|-\n|[[1979 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1979]]\n|{{sortname|James|Callaghan}}\n|31.6\n|{{composition bar|17|78|#DA251D}}\n|\n|2nd\n|-\n|[[1984 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1984]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{sortname|Neil|Kinnock}}\n|34.7\n|{{composition bar|32|78|#DA251D}}\n|{{increase}} 15\n|{{steady}} 2nd\n|-\n|[[1989 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1989]]\n|40.1\n|{{composition bar|45|78|#DA251D}}\n|{{increase}} 13\n|{{increase}} 1st\n|-\n|[[1994 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1994]]\n|{{sortname|Margaret|Beckett}}<br>(interim)\n|42.6\n|{{composition bar|62|84|#DA251D}}\n|{{increase}} 17\n|{{steady}} 1st\n|-\n|[[1999 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|1999]]<ref group=\"fn\">Electoral system changed from first past the post to proportional representation.</ref>\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{sortname|Tony|Blair}}\n|28.0\n|{{composition bar|29|84|#DA251D}}\n|{{decrease}} 33\n|{{decrease}} 2nd\n|-\n|[[2004 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|2004]]\n|22.6\n|{{composition bar|19|78|#DA251D}}\n|{{decrease}} 6\n|{{steady}} 2nd\n|-\n|[[2009 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|2009]]\n|{{sortname|Gordon|Brown}}\n|15.7\n|{{composition bar|13|72|#DA251D}}\n|{{decrease}} 5\n|{{decrease}} 3rd\n|-\n|[[2014 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|2014]]\n|{{sortname|Ed|Miliband}}\n|24.4\n|{{composition bar|20|73|#DA251D}}\n|{{increase}} 7\n|{{increase}} 2nd\n|-\n|[[2019 European Parliament election in the United Kingdom|2019]]\n|{{sortname|Jeremy|Corbyn}}\n|13.6\n|{{c