s permanently unavailable, the deputy leader shall automatically become party leader on a pro-tem basis.|journal=|access-date=26 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025093405/http://researchbriefings.files.parliament.uk/documents/SN03938/SN03938.pdf|archive-date=25 October 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Tony Blair]] (1994\u20132007)\n* [[Gordon Brown]] (2007\u20132010)\n** [[Harriet Harman]] (2010; acting)<ref name=\"rule\"/>\n* [[Ed Miliband]] (2010\u20132015)\n** [[Harriet Harman]] (2015; acting)\n* [[Jeremy Corbyn]] ([[2015 Labour Party leadership election (UK)|2015]]\u2013[[2020 Labour Party leadership election|2020]])\n* [[Keir Starmer]] (2020\u2013present){{div col end}}\n\n=== Living former Labour Party leaders ===\n{{As of|2020|04}}, there are seven living former Labour Party leaders.\n<gallery class=\"centre\">\nFile:Kinnock, Neil.jpg|[[Neil Kinnock]]<br>(1983\u20131992)<br>born 1942 (age {{age|1942|3|28}})\nFile:Official portrait of Margaret Beckett crop 2.jpg|[[Margaret Beckett]]<br>(1994; interim)<br>born 1943 (age {{age|1943|1|15}})\nFile:MSC 2014 Blair Mueller MSC2014 (cropped).jpg|[[Tony Blair]]<br>([[Premiership of Tony Blair|1994\u20132007]])<br>born 1953 (age {{age|1953|5|6}})\nFile:Gordon Brown official.jpg|[[Gordon Brown]]<br>([[Premiership of Gordon Brown|2007\u20132010]])<br>born 1951 (age {{age|1951|2|20}})\nFile:Harriet Harman.jpg|[[Harriet Harman]]<br>(2010 and 2015; interim)<br>born 1950 (age {{age|1950|7|30}})\nFile:Official portrait of Edward Miliband crop 2 retouch.jpg|[[Ed Miliband]]<br>(2010\u20132015)<br>born 1969 (age {{age|1969|12|24}})\nFile:Jeremy Corbyn election infobox 2.jpg|[[Jeremy Corbyn]]<br>(2015\u20132020)<br>born 1949 (age {{age|1949|05|26}})\n</gallery>\n\n=== Deputy Leaders of the Labour Party since 1922 ===\n{{main|Deputy Leader of the Labour Party (UK)}}\n{{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[John Robert Clynes]] (1922\u20131932)\n* [[William Graham (Edinburgh MP)|William Graham]] (1931\u20131932)\n*