reenwich]]\n| [[Lewisham]]\n|\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2212|name1= }}\n| [[Lee Green]]\n| [[Bromley]]\n|\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2213|name1= }}\n| [[Blackheath, London|Blackheath]]\n| [[Eltham]]\n|\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2214|name1= }}\n| [[Brixton]]\n| [[New Cross]]\n| In the London Borough of Lambeth: Morval Road, Dalberg Road, Brixton Water Lane, Dulwich Road, Half Moon Lane; in the London Borough of Southwark: Half Moon Lane, Village Way, East Dulwich Grove, East Dulwich Road, Nunhead Lane, Evelina Road; in the London Borough of Lewisham: Evelina Road, Lausanne Road\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2215|name1= }}\n| [[Peckham]]\n| [[Peckham Rye]]\n| \n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2216|name1= }}\n| [[Sydenham, London|Sydenham]]\n| [[Denmark Hill]]\n|\n|- \n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2217|name1= }}\n| [[Clapham Common]]\n| [[Camberwell]]\n| In the London Borough of Lambeth: Clapham Park Road, Acre Lane, Coldharbour Lane;  in the London Borough of Southwark: Coldharbour Lane\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2218|name1= }}\n| [[Sydenham, London|Sydenham]]\n| Bell Green, Sydenham\n|\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2219|name1= }}\n| [[Crawley]]\n| Crawley\n| \n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2220|name1= }}\n| [[Copthorne, West Sussex|Copthorne]]\n| [[Crawley]]\n|\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2260|name1= }}\n| [[Southfleet]]\n| [[Northfleet]] \n|  \n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2270|name1= }}\n| [[Polegate]]\n| [[Eastbourne]]\n| \n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2280|name1= }}\n| [[Eastbourne]]\n| [[Eastbourne]]\n| Cross levels Way from Kings Drive to Lottbridge Drove and A22 junction for Golden Jubilee Way.\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2290|name1= }}\n| [[Eastbourne]]\n| Eastbourne\n| Short link road\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2300|name1= }}\n| [[Burgess Hill]]\n| [[Twineham#Hickstead|Hickstead]]\n| \n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2310|name1= }}\n| Unused\n|\n| erroneously shown on maps from [[Brompton, Kent]] to [[Medway Tunnel]]. That is actually the C372.\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2500|name1= }}\n| Cowstead Farm\n| [[Eastchurch]]\n| \n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2590|name1= }}\n| Reserved\n| \n| Reserved for former A259 in Bexhill when bypass is complete.\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2690|name1= }}\n| [[Bexhill-on-Sea|Bexhill]]\n| [[Hastings]]\n| Created 2015.\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2691|name1= }}\n| [[Bexhill-on-Sea|Bexhill]]\n| [[Bexhill-on-Sea|Bexhill]]\n| Created 2019.\n|-\n| {{Jct|country=GBR|A|2700|noshield=y}}\n| [[A27 road|A27]], [[Worthing]]\n| [[Worthing West (UK Parliament constituency)|West Worthing]]\n|Technically the route hasn't adopted its A number and remains a C status road with the number C37 (West Sussex). Some road signs in the local area say A2700, but are covered up. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sabre-roads.org.uk/wiki/index.php?title=A2700|title=A2700 - Roader's Digest: The SABRE Wiki|website=www.sabre-roads.org.uk|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2990|name1= }}\n| [[Yorkletts]]\n| [[Herne Bay, Kent|Herne Bay]]\n| \n|}\n{{commons category|A roads in Zone 2 of the Great Britain numbering scheme}}\n\n{{United Kingdom roads}}\n\n[[Category:Roads in England| 2]]\n[[Category:Lists of roads in the United Kingdom|2]]\n\n<references />\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2013}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2013}}\n[[File:United Kingdom A road zones.svg|thumb|200px|The numbering zones for A-roads in Great Britain]]\nList of [[A roads in Great Britain|A road]]s in [[List of A roads zones in Great Britain|zone]] 2 in [[Great Britain]] starting south of the [[River Thames]] and east of the [[A3 road (Great Britain)|A3]] (roads beginning with 2).\n__FORCETOC__\n\n==Single- and double-digit roads==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=100px| Road\n! width=\"20%\"|From\n! width=\"20%\"|To\n! Notes\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|2|noshield1=|nolink1= }}\n| [[Borough, London|The Borough]], [[Central London]]\n| [[Dover]]\n| The section between Three Crutches (east of Gravesend) and Brenley Corner (near Faversham) ha