alized in 1922, and the number was instead used on the road from the A275 in to the A26 in [[Lewes]] that day. That road became part of the rerouted A275, while the old route of the A275 became the A2029.\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|277|name1= }}\n| [[Lewes]]\n|\n| [[Lewes Town Road]], connecting the [[A26 road|A26]] and the [[A27 road|A27]]; formerly part of the A27. The original alignment went from [[Brighton]] to [[Portslade|Portslade-by-Sea]] (became part of extended B2066 and B2194).\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|278|name1= }}\n| [[Rainham, Kent|Rainham]]\n| [[Bredhurst]]\n| Previously allocated to a road between [[Felbridge]] and [[Horsham]] (now part of the A264).\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|279|name1= }}\n| Unused\n|\n| Previously a road between [[Handcross]] and [[Lower Beeding]]. Downgraded to a B-class road, an extension of the B2110, while the A279 spur became part of an extended B2115.\n|- \n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|280|name1= }}\n| [[Findon, West Sussex|Findon]]\n| [[Angmering]]\n| Originally allocated to a road from A281 to A279 (now part of the B2110) in in Lower Beeding; this became a spur of the A279 (now part of the B2115) in 1935 when the current A280 was created as an upgrade of the B2140.\n|- \n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|281|name1= }} \n| [[Guildford]]\n| [[Pyecombe]]\n|\n|- \n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|282|noshield1=|nolink1= }}\n| [[Darenth]]\n| [[Thurrock]]\n| Part of the London Orbital ([[M25 motorway|M25]]). Previously allocated to a road between [[Broadbridge Heath]] and [[Five Oaks]] (now part of the A264).\n|- \n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|283|name1= }} \n| [[Milford, Surrey|Milford]]\n| [[Shoreham-by-Sea]]\n|\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|284|name1= }}\n| [[Houghton, West Sussex|Houghton]]\n| [[Littlehampton]]\n| \n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|285|name1= }}\n| [[Petworth]]\n| [[Chichester]]\n|\n|- \n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|286|name1= }}\n| [[Milford, Surrey|Milford]]\n| [[Birdham]]\n|\n|-\n| {{jct|country=GBR|A|287|name1= }}\n| [[Hook, Hart|Hook]]\n| [[Haslemere]]\n|