etts]]\n| [[Herne Bay, Kent|Herne Bay]]\n| \n|}\n{{commons category|A roads in Zone 2 of the Great Britain numbering scheme}}\n\n{{United Kingdom roads}}\n\n[[Category:Roads in England| 2]]\n[[Category:Lists of roads in the United Kingdom|2]]\n\n<references />\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:Golden Cross\u2192Golden Cross, East Sussex,Bexhill\u2192Bexhill-on-Sea(3)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_roads_in_Zone_2_of_the_Great_Britain_numbering_scheme"}
{"title_page": "Peter Niemeyer", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Peter Niemeyer\n| image = Peter Niemeyer 18.jpg\n| image_size = 200px\n| caption = Niemeyer in 2010\n| fullname = Peter Niemeyer\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1983|11|22|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[H\u00f6rstel]], [[West Germany]]\n| height = 1.88m\n| currentclub = \n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|Defensive midfielder]], [[Defender (association football)#Centre back|centre back]]\n| youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}\u20131996 | youthclubs1 = Teuto Riesenbeck\n| youthyears2 = 1996\u20131999 | youthclubs2 = Borussia Emsdetten\n| youthyears3 = 1999\u20132002 | youthclubs3 = [[FC Twente|Twente]]\n| years1 = 2002\u20132007 | clubs1 = [[FC Twente|Twente]]                     | caps1 = 106 | goals1 = 4\n| years2 = 2007\u20132011 | clubs2 = [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]]       | caps2 = 32  | goals2 = 2\n| years3 = 2007\u20132010 | clubs3 = [[SV Werder Bremen II|Werder Bremen II]] | caps3 = 12  | goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2010\u20132011 | clubs4 = \u2192 [[Hertha BSC]] (loan)                  | caps4 = 28  | goals4 = 3\n| years5 = 2011\u20132015 | clubs5 = [[Hertha BSC]]                           | caps5 = 93  | goals5 = 6\n| years6 = 2015\u20132018 | clubs6 = [[SV Darmstadt 98|Darmstadt 98]]         | caps6 = 50  | goals6 = 2\n| totalcaps = 321\n| totalgoals = 18\n| nationalyears1 = 2005\u20132006\n| nationalteam1 = [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U21]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 6\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Peter Niemeyer''' (born 22 November 1983) is a German former professional [[Association football|footballer]]. Mainly a [[Midfielder#Defensive|defensive midfielder]], he can also operate as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre back|central defender]].\n\n==Club career==\nAlthough born in Germany, Niemeyer spent the first years of his professional career in the Netherlands, playing for [[Eredivisie]]'s [[FC Twente]]. In mid-January 2007, he joined [[Bundesliga]] side [[SV Werder Bremen]], appearing in three league games for the main squad during [[2006\u201307 Bundesliga|his first season]].\n\nOn 29 September 2007, Niemeyer participated in the 8\u20131 home crushing of [[Arminia Bielefeld]], scoring the game opener and his first Bundesliga goal. Incidentally, he also limped out of the match, after just 33 minutes.\n\nIn the [[2008\u201309 Bundesliga|2008\u201309 season]], Niemeyer appeared in a career-best 25 official games, including five in the [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]], as Werder [[2008\u201309 UEFA Cup|reached]] [[2009 UEFA Cup Final|the final]] against [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]], where he started in a 1\u20132 [[Overtime (sports)|overtime]] loss.\n\nOn 9 August 2010, Niemeyer moved on loan to [[Hertha BSC]], who were relegated to the [[2. Bundesliga|second division]] [[2009\u201310 Bundesliga|the season before]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.berlinonline.de/berliner-kurier/print/sport/314770.html | title = Hertha zahlt 200.000 Euro f\u00fcr Niemeyer |trans-title=Hertha pays 200.000 Euros for Niemeyer | language = German | publisher = Berlin Online | date = 9 August 2010}}{{Dead link|date=August 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 August 2015, Niemeyer signed for recently promoted [[SV Darmstadt 98]] in the Bundesliga on a three-year deal.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.sv98.de/home/lilien/aktuelles/nachrichten-ansicht/news/lilien-verpflichten-peter-niemeyer-von-hertha-bsc/ | title = Lilien verpflichten Peter Niemeyer von Hertha BSC | language = German | publisher = SV Darmstadt 98 | accessdate = 3 August 2015 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150806004607/http://www.sv98.de/home/lilien/aktuelles/nachrichten-ansicht/news/lilien-verpflichten-peter-niemeyer-von-hertha-bsc/ | archivedate = 6 August 2015 }}</ref> On 1 September 2018, after the closing of the 2018 summer transfer window, he announced he had not received an offer to renew his contract and would leave the club.<ref>{{cite news |title=Niemeyers Zeit am B\u00f6lle ist zu Ende |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/2bundesliga/startseite/730845/artikel_niemeyers-zeit-am-boelle-ist-zu-ende.html |accessdate=1 September 2018 |work=kicker Online |date=1 September 2018 |language=German}}</ref>\n\nNiemeyer retired shortly afterwards.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jahn |first1=Michael |title=Ex-Hertha-Kapit\u00e4n Peter Niemeyer: \u201eDas Relegationsspiel war unm\u00f6glich\u201c |url=https://www.berliner-kurier.de/sport/hertha-bsc/ex-hertha-kapitaen-peter-niemeyer---das-relegationsspiel-war-unmoeglich--31544860 |accessdate=2 January 2019 |work=Berliner Kurier |date=6 November 2018 |language=German}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club!!rowspan=\"2\"|Season!!colspan=\"3\"|League!!colspan=\"2\"|Cup{{ref|a|1}}!!colspan=\"2\"|Continental{{ref|a|2}}!!colspan=\"2\"|Other{{ref|a|3}}!!colspan=\"2\"|Total!!rowspan=\"2\"|{{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[FC Twente|Twente]]||[[2002\u201303 FC Twente season|2002\u201303]]||rowspan=\"5\"|[[Eredivisie]]||3||0||<!-- Cup appearances -->||<!-- Cup goals -->||rowspan=\"4\" colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||rowspan=\"3\" colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||3||0||<ref name=\"Peter Niemeyer \u00bb Club matches\">{{cite web|title=Peter Niemeyer \u00bb Club matches|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/peter-niemeyer/2/|publisher=World Football|accessdate=5 May 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2003\u201304 FC Twente season|2003\u201304]]||31||1||<!-- Cup appearances -->||<!-- Cup goals -->||31||1||<ref name=\"Peter Niemeyer \u00bb Club matches\"/>\n|-\n|[[2004\u201305 FC Twente season|2004\u201305]]||27||1||<!-- Cup appearances -->||<!-- Cup goals -->||27||1||<ref name=\"Peter Niemeyer \u00bb Club matches\"/>\n